OVERVIEW:
This simulation is for a deterministic Turing Machine with a bi-infinite tape. It is designed to be highly reliable, taking an encoding of a Turing machine's states and alphabet along with an input string, and executing transitions until a designated halting state is activated.

INCLUDED FILES:
* tm/Direction.java - Contains the enumeration for left and right tape movements.
* tm/Tape.java - Implements the dynamic storage for the machine's bi-infinite tape using a Map to represent content efficiently.
* tm/TM.java - Defines the control logic and states of the turing machine based on the given parameters.
* tm/TMInterface.java - Basic interface for TM simulator methods.
* tm/TMSimulator.java - The main entry point to parse standard input files and manage the simulation.
* tm/TMState.java - Represents an individual state in the turing machine and its associated transitions. 
* tm/Transition.java - The instruction template specifying the next state, written symbol, and tape head direction.

COMPILING AND RUNNING:
To compile the files, execute the following from the root directory:
  $ javac tm/*.java

To run the simulator, provide the name of the input text file describing the TM and tape content:
  $ java tm.TMSimulator file0.txt
